  %div{"data-role" => "header"}
    %h1 .selector
  #selector1.ui-body-c{"data-role" => "content"}
    %h2.jq-clearfix.roundTop.section-title
      %span.name selector
      %span.returns
        Returns:
        %a.return{:href => "http://docs.jquery.com/Types#String"} String
    .jq-box.roundBottom.entry-details
      %p.desc
        %strong> Description:
        A selector representing selector originally passed to jQuery().
      %ul.signatures
        %li#selector.signature
          %h4.name
            %span.versionAdded>
              version added:
              %a{:href => "/category/version/1.3/"} 1.3
            selector
      .longdesc
        %p Should be used in conjunction with context to determine the exact query used.
        %p
          The
          %code .live()
          method for binding event handlers uses this property to determine how to perform its searches. Plug-ins which perform similar tasks may also find the property useful. This property contains a string representing the matched set of elements, but if DOM traversal methods have been called on the object, the string may not be a valid jQuery selector expression. For this reason, the value of
          %code .selector
          is generally most useful immediately following the original creation of the object. Consequently, the
          %code .live()
          method should only be used in this scenario.
      %h3 Examples:
      #entry-examples.entry-examples
        #example-0
          %h4
            Example:
            %span.desc Determine the selector used.
          %pre
            %code.example.demo-code
              :preserve
                &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
                &lt;html&gt;
                &lt;head&gt;
                  &lt;style&gt;
                  body { cursor:pointer; }
                  div { width:50px; height:30px; margin:5px; float:left;
                        background:green; }
                  span { color:red; }
                  &lt;/style&gt;
                  &lt;script src="http://code.jquery.com/jquery-latest.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
                &lt;/head&gt;
                &lt;body&gt;
                	Some selectors:&lt;ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;
                &lt;script&gt;$("ul")
                  .append("&lt;li&gt;" + $("ul").selector + "&lt;/li&gt;")
                  .append("&lt;li&gt;" + $("ul li").selector + "&lt;/li&gt;")
                  .append("&lt;li&gt;" + $("div#foo ul:not([class])").selector + "&lt;/li&gt;");
                
                &lt;/script&gt;
                &lt;/body&gt;
                &lt;/html&gt;          %h4 Demo:
          .demo.code-demo
        #example-1
          %h4
            Example:
            %span.desc Collecting elements differently
          %pre
            %code.example.demo-code
              :preserve
                &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
                &lt;html&gt;
                &lt;head&gt;
                  &lt;script src="http://code.jquery.com/jquery-latest.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
                &lt;/head&gt;
                &lt;body&gt;
                	Some selectors:&lt;ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;
                
                &lt;script&gt;
                   $('&lt;div&gt;' + $('ul li.foo').selector + '&lt;/div&gt;').appendTo('body');  // "ul li.foo"
                   $('&lt;div&gt;' + $('ul').find('li').filter('.foo').selector + '&lt;/div&gt;').appendTo('body'); // "ul li.filter(.foo)"
                &lt;/script&gt;
                &lt;/body&gt;
                &lt;/html&gt;          %h4 Demo:
          .demo.code-demo
